  <p class="boxtext">

  <strong>Relative and Absolute Positioning</strong>
The outer box is defined as a DIV and is relatively positioned. As such it becomes a <em>containing block</em>. No attempt is made to set any values for top, left, bottom or right.  Each corner box is also created using a DIV but each is absolutely positioned and occurs within the outer box. Because of this they position themselves in relation to the edges of the <em>containing block</em>. Observe what happens if you add or remove text from this paragraph. Also, observe the effect of moving any of the corner DIVs outside the containing DIVThe outer box is defined as a DIV and is relatively positioned. As such it becomes a <em>containing block</em>. No attempt is made to set any values for top, left, bottom or right.  Each corner box is also created using a DIV but each is absolutely positioned and occurs within the outer box. Because of this they position themselves in relation to the edges of the <em>containing block</em>. Observe what happens if you add or remove text from this paragraph. Also, observe the effect of moving any of the corner DIVs outside the containing DIV.
